}
```

The fix matches the established pattern used in the mount-time `loadSession` catch block (lines 646-649) and other handlers throughout the file. When the `GET /api/training/:tenant/session` call fails inside `refreshSession`, the user now sees the error message "Unable to load your training session. Please check your connection and try again." rendered by `renderError`, instead of the function silently returning with no user feedback. The `finally` block that clears `conflictMessage` still runs in all cases.

